We utilize third-party foundries and component suppliers to manufacture or supply a number of our products and components necessary for our products that we manufacture. As part of our strategy, we expect to continue to rely upon third-party foundries. Delays in the development of foundries' future manufacturing processes could delay the introduction of products or components we design for such processes, and insufficient foundry capacity could prevent us from meeting customer demand. We typically have less control over delivery schedules, design and manufacturing co-optimization, yields, quality, product quantities and costs for components and products that are manufactured by third parties.", 'score': 0.5544513}, {'ticker': 'NVDA', 'year': 2026, 'item': 'Item 1A', 'header_path': 'NVDA / 2026 / Part I / Item 1A. Risk Factors / Risks Related to Demand, Supply, and Manufacturing', 'chunk_index': 36, 'text': '### Risks Related to Demand, Supply, and Manufacturing

